results.description: This was one I took a long time ago. This was an early morning shot from one of my birding trips out at Elmer W. Oliver. This was one of the better shots of the bird but it was still during the time I didn't really know how to change the settings on my camera. Still a very cool shot of a Sapsucker. I don't see these guys that often in the winter time. Still going through the old SD card and Thumb drives for stragglers. I have found so many photos that have not been put into the system yet which really stinks.
